Kristalina Georgieva, Managing Director, International Monetary Fund, Gediminas Šimkus, Chairman of the Board, Bank of Lithuania, Delina Ibrahimaj, Minister of Finance and Economy, Albania, Teresa Czerwińska, Vice-President, European Investment Bank with the moderator Ali Aslan discussed how the energy crisis has affected CESEE economies, the short- and medium-term challenges for the region, and policies that could mitigate them.